<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Canon R10 + Sigma 18-50mm f/2.8 — Field Guide</title>
<style>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Space+Mono:wght@400;700&display=swap');

  :root {
    --black: #0D0D0D;
    --off-white: #F5F3EE;
    --warm-mid: #E8E3DA;
    --gold: #C8922A;
    --gold-light: #F2C96A;
    --red: #C0392B;
    --teal: #1A7A72;
    --blue: #1A4B7A;
    --ink: #1C1C1C;
    --muted: #6B6560;
  }

  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  body {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--off-white);
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* ── COVER ── */
  .cover {
    background: var(--black);
    padding: 48px 32px 40px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--gold);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .cover::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: -60px; right: -60px;
    width: 280px; height: 280px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(200,146,42,0.18) 0%, transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .cover-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .cover h1 {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 6vw, 42px);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .cover h1 span { color: var(--gold); }
  .cover-sub {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 13px;
    max-width: 480px;
  }
  .cover-tags {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }
  .tag {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border: 1px solid;
    border-radius: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .tag-gold { border-color: var(--gold); color: var(--gold); }
  .tag-teal { border-color: var(--teal); color: var(--teal); }
  .tag-red  { border-color: var(--red);  color: var(--red);  }
  .tag-blue { border-color: var(--blue); color: #5B9BD5; }

  /* ── SECTIONS ── */
  .section {
    padding: 32px 24px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
  }
  .section-label {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .section h2 {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  /* ── EXPOSURE TRIANGLE ── */
  .triangle-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .tri-card {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 16px 12px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .tri-card .icon {
    font-size: 22px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    display: block;
  }
  .tri-card h3 {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .tri-card p { font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.4; }
  .tri-card .values {
    margin-top: 10px;
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--gold-light);
  }

  /* ── SCENE CARDS ── */
  .scene-card {
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .scene-outdoor { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a2a1a 0%, #0d3d28 100%); border-left: 3px solid var(--teal); }
  .scene-indoor  { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #162040 100%); border-left: 3px solid #5B9BD5; }
  .scene-lowlight{ background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a0a0a 0%, #2a1010 100%); border-left: 3px solid var(--red); }

  .scene-card h3 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .scene-card h3 .dot {
    width: 8px; height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .dot-teal { background: var(--teal); }
  .dot-blue { background: #5B9BD5; }
  .dot-red  { background: var(--red); }

  .settings-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .setting-pill {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 8px 10px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .setting-pill .label {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }
  .setting-pill .value {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--gold-light);
  }
  .scene-tips {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    padding-top: 10px;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }
  .scene-tips strong { color: var(--off-white); }

  /* ── ISO TABLE ── */
  .iso-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 12px;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }
  .iso-table th {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-align: left;
    padding: 8px 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
  }
  .iso-table td {
    padding: 10px 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .iso-table td:first-child {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--gold-light);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .iso-bar {
    height: 4px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    margin-top: 4px;
    background: var(--gold);
  }

  /* ── APERTURE CHART ── */
  .aperture-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 8px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
  }
  .aperture-value {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--gold-light);
    width: 52px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .aperture-visual {
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .aperture-circle {
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: rgba(200,146,42,0.25);
    border: 2px solid var(--gold);
  }
  .aperture-desc {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--off-white);
  }
  .aperture-desc span {
    display: block;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 1px;
  }

  /* ── QUICK FIXES ── */
  .fix-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .fix-card {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 14px;
  }
  .fix-problem {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--red);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 5px;
  }
  .fix-solution {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .fix-solution code {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    background: rgba(200,146,42,0.15);
    color: var(--gold-light);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  /* ── EXERCISES ── */
  .exercise {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    padding: 18px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .exercise-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .exercise-num {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--gold);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .exercise h3 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }
  .exercise-level {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .level-beginner { color: var(--teal); }
  .level-mid      { color: var(--gold); }
  .level-pressure { color: var(--red); }

  .exercise-body {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .exercise-goal {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--gold-light);
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    padding-top: 8px;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }

  /* ── MODES REFERENCE ── */
  .modes-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .mode-card {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 14px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
  }
  .mode-dial {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .mode-card h3 {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .mode-card p {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
  .mode-card .use-when {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--gold-light);
    margin-top: 6px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── PRESSURE PROTOCOL ── */
  .protocol-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    padding: 14px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .protocol-step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .step-num {
    width: 28px; height: 28px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--gold);
    color: var(--black);
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .step-content h4 {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .step-content p {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .step-content code {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    background: rgba(200,146,42,0.15);
    color: var(--gold-light);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  /* ── FOOTER ── */
  .footer {
    padding: 28px 24px;
    text-align: center;
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }
  .footer strong { color: var(--gold); }

  /* ── DIVIDER ── */
  .divider {
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--gold), transparent);
    margin: 4px 0;
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  .highlight-box {
    background: rgba(200,146,42,0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(200,146,42,0.3);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 14px;
    margin-top: 14px;
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--off-white);
  }
  .highlight-box strong { color: var(--gold-light); }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- COVER -->
<div class="cover">
  <div class="cover-eyebrow">LaVidaRicia · Field Guide v1.0</div>
  <h1>Canon R10 + Sigma 18-50mm<br><span>Master Your Light</span></h1>
  <p class="cover-sub">Settings cheat sheets, aperture & ISO references, and skill-building exercises to get you off Auto — for good.</p>
  <div class="cover-tags">
    <span class="tag tag-teal">Outdoor</span>
    <span class="tag tag-blue">Indoor</span>
    <span class="tag tag-red">Low Light</span>
    <span class="tag tag-gold">Portraits</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- EXPOSURE TRIANGLE -->
<div class="section">
  <div class="section-label">The Foundation</div>
  <h2>The Exposure Triangle</h2>
  <p style="font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:16px;">Every photo is controlled by three things working together. Master these and you'll never be stuck on Auto again.</p>

  <div class="triangle-grid">
    <div class="tri-card">
      <span class="icon">🔆</span>
      <h3>ISO</h3>
      <p>How sensitive the sensor is to light. Higher = brighter but grainier.</p>
      <div class="values">100 → 6400+</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tri-card">
      <span class="icon">◎</span>
      <h3>Aperture</h3>
      <p>Size of the lens opening. Lower f/ = more light + more blur.</p>
      <div class="values">f/1.8 → f/16</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tri-card">
      <span class="icon">⏱</span>
      <h3>Shutter</h3>
      <p>How long the sensor is exposed. Faster = freezes motion.</p>
      <div class="values">1/30 → 1/2000</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="highlight-box">
    <strong>The golden rule:</strong> When one goes up, something else must compensate. Got darker? Raise ISO or open aperture wider. Got blurry motion? Increase shutter speed then raise ISO to compensate. They're always in conversation.
  </div>
</div>

<!-- CAMERA MODES -->
<div class="section">
  <div class="section-label">Dial Reference</div>
  <h2>Which Mode to Use When</h2>
  <div class="modes-grid">
    <div class="mode-card">
      <div class="mode-dial">Av</div>
      <h3>Aperture Priority</h3>
      <p>You control the aperture (blur). Camera handles shutter speed.</p>
      <p class="use-when">→ Your default mode for 90% of shooting</p>
    </div>
    <div class="mode-card">
      <div class="mode-dial">Tv</div>
      <h3>Shutter Priority</h3>
      <p>You control shutter speed. Camera handles aperture.</p>
      <p class="use-when">→ Moving subjects, dancing, kids running</p>
    </div>
    <div class="mode-card">
      <div class="mode-dial">M</div>
      <h3>Manual</h3>
      <p>You control everything. Full creative control.</p>
      <p class="use-when">→ Studio, controlled light, or when you're ready</p>
    </div>
    <div class="mode-card">
      <div class="mode-dial">P</div>
      <h3>Program Auto</h3>
      <p>Camera picks both, but you can still shift the combo.</p>
      <p class="use-when">→ Fast moving situations, backup mode</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top:12px;">
    <strong>Start here:</strong> Put the dial on <strong>Av</strong>. Set your aperture, and let the camera handle shutter. This alone gives you creative control over blur and light while removing the biggest variable. This is how most photographers shoot day-to-day.
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SCENE CHEAT SHEETS -->
<div class="section">
  <div class="section-label">Scene Cheat Sheets</div>
  <h2>Settings by Scene</h2>

  <!-- OUTDOOR -->
  <div class="scene-card scene-outdoor">
    <h3><span class="dot dot-teal"></span>☀️ Outdoor — Bright / Golden Hour</h3>
    <div class="settings-row">
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">ISO</div>
        <div class="value">100–400</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Aperture</div>
        <div class="value">f/2.8–f/5.6</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Shutter</div>
        <div class="value">1/500–1/2000</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="settings-row">
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">White Bal</div>
        <div class="value">Daylight</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">AF Mode</div>
        <div class="value">Face+Track</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Metering</div>
        <div class="value">Evaluative</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="scene-tips">
      <strong>Portrait tip:</strong> Open aperture to f/2.8 for background blur. Stand with subject's back to sun (backlit) for a soft glow, or find open shade for even skin tones. Avoid harsh midday direct sun — it creates unflattering shadows under eyes. · <strong>Bright override:</strong> If image is too bright, press the Exposure Compensation button (the ± button) and dial to -1/3 or -2/3.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- OUTDOOR OVERCAST -->
  <div class="scene-card scene-outdoor" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #151f25 0%, #1c2d35 100%);">
    <h3><span class="dot dot-teal"></span>🌥 Outdoor — Overcast / Cloudy</h3>
    <div class="settings-row">
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">ISO</div>
        <div class="value">200–800</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Aperture</div>
        <div class="value">f/2.8–f/4</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Shutter</div>
        <div class="value">1/200–1/800</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="settings-row">
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">White Bal</div>
        <div class="value">Cloudy</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">AF Mode</div>
        <div class="value">Face+Track</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Metering</div>
        <div class="value">Evaluative</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="scene-tips">
      <strong>Hidden gem:</strong> Overcast skies are a giant softbox — this is actually the best natural light for portraits. Skin looks smooth and shadows are soft. Open your aperture wide (f/2.8) and shoot freely. Set White Balance to "Cloudy" to warm up the cool, grey light.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- INDOOR -->
  <div class="scene-card scene-indoor">
    <h3><span class="dot dot-blue"></span>🏠 Indoor — Window Light / Daytime</h3>
    <div class="settings-row">
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">ISO</div>
        <div class="value">400–1600</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Aperture</div>
        <div class="value">f/2.8</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Shutter</div>
        <div class="value">1/100–1/320</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="settings-row">
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">White Bal</div>
        <div class="value">Auto / Cloudy</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">AF Mode</div>
        <div class="value">Face+Track</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Metering</div>
        <div class="value">Spot / Eval</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="scene-tips">
      <strong>Window light trick:</strong> Position your subject facing the window (not beside it). The light becomes your "studio light." Stand between subject and window — you'll get catch lights in their eyes. If background is too bright vs. face, use Spot Metering on their face and Exposure Comp +1/3.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- INDOOR ARTIFICIAL -->
  <div class="scene-card scene-indoor" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #12101e 0%, #1a1530 100%);">
    <h3><span class="dot dot-blue"></span>💡 Indoor — Artificial / Mixed Light</h3>
    <div class="settings-row">
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">ISO</div>
        <div class="value">800–3200</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Aperture</div>
        <div class="value">f/2.8</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Shutter</div>
        <div class="value">1/60–1/160</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="settings-row">
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">White Bal</div>
        <div class="value">Tungsten/Auto</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">AF Mode</div>
        <div class="value">Face+Track</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Metering</div>
        <div class="value">Spot</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="scene-tips">
      <strong>The fix for "yellow" photos:</strong> Set White Balance to "Tungsten" (the lightbulb icon) to neutralize warm artificial light. Still off? Use "Auto WB" — on the R10 it's excellent. Shutter speed must stay at <strong>1/60 minimum</strong> indoors or you'll get motion blur even standing still.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- LOW LIGHT -->
  <div class="scene-card scene-lowlight">
    <h3><span class="dot dot-red"></span>🌙 Low Light — Evening / Dimly Lit Spaces</h3>
    <div class="settings-row">
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">ISO</div>
        <div class="value">1600–6400</div>
      </div>
      <div class="setting-pill">
        <div class="label">Aperture</div>
